"title": "5358: judges",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5358",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Individuals responsible for the administration of justice and/or the operation of government. In the OT the term “judge” is also used in a special sense meaning a leader of Israel. God is portrayed in Scripture as the judge of all the earth; in the NT Jesus Christ is presented as the judge appointed by God.</p>\n<h2>Judges as leaders of Israel</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam7:15\">1SA 7:15</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg2:16-Judg2:19\">JDG 2:16–2:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg3:9-Judg3:11\">JDG 3:9–3:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg4:4-Judg4:10\">JDG 4:4–4:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ruth1:1\">RUT 1:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs23:22\">2KI 23:22</a></p>\n<h2>The role of judges</h2>\n<h3>Judicial and punitive</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut25:1-Deut25:2\">DEU 25:1–25:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen19:6-Gen19:9\">GEN 19:6–19:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod18:13-Exod18:26\">EXO 18:13–18:26</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod22:7-Exod22:9\">EXO 22:7–22:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num25:5\">NUM 25:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut1:16\">DEU 1:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut19:16-Deut19:21\">DEU 19:16–19:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut21:1-Deut21:2\">DEU 21:1–21:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr19:5-2Chr19:7\">2CH 19:5–19:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek44:24\">EZK 44:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke12:14\">LUK 12:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor6:2-1Cor6:5\">1CO 6:2–6:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev20:4\">REV 20:4</a></p>\n<h3>Administrative</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod21:2-Exod21:6\">EXO 21:2–21:6</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra10:14\">EZR 10:14</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts24:10\">ACT 24:10</a></p>\n<h2>The status of judges in ancient Israel</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh8:33\">JOS 8:33</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh23:1-Josh24:1\">JOS 23:1–24:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs23:22\">2KI 23:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr1:2-2Chr1:3\">2CH 1:2–1:3</a></p>\n<h2>The jurisdiction of judges</h2>\n<h3>Local judges</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut16:18\">DEU 16:18</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr19:5\">2CH 19:5</a></p>\n<h3>Judges with national authority</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam7:15-1Sam7:17\">1SA 7:15–7:17</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut17:8-Deut17:9\">DEU 17:8–17:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam15:4\">2SA 15:4</a></p>\n<h2>Regulations relating to judges</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut1:16\">DEU 1:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut17:12\">DEU 17:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut25:2-Deut25:3\">DEU 25:2–25:3</a></p>\n<h2>Corrupt judges</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mic7:3\">MIC 7:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke18:2-Luke18:8\">LUK 18:2–18:8</a></p>\n<h2>Levitical judges</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek44:24\">EZK 44:24</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr23:3-1Chr23:4\">1CH 23:3–23:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr26:29\">1CH 26:29</a></p>\n<h2>Judges during periods of foreign rule</h2>\n<h3>Under the Babylonian empire</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan3:2-Dan3:3\">DAN 3:2–3:3</a></strong></p>\n<h3>Under the Medo-Persian empire</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra7:25\">EZR 7:25</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra4:9\">EZR 4:9</a></p>\n<h3>Under the Roman Empire</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt27:19\">MAT 27:19</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt5:25\">MAT 5:25</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke12:58\">LUK 12:58</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John19:13\">JHN 19:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts24:10\">ACT 24:10</a></p>\n<h2>God as judge</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa33:22\">ISA 33:22</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg11:27\">JDG 11:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam24:12\">1SA 24:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam24:15\">1SA 24:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs8:31-1Kgs8:32\">1KI 8:31–8:32</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr16:33\">1CH 16:33</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job9:15\">JOB 9:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps58:11\">PSA 58:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps94:2\">PSA 94:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John8:50\">JHN 8:50</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John12:48\">JHN 12:48</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb12:23\">HEB 12:23</a></p>\n<h3>The righteousness of God's judgment</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen18:25\">GEN 18:25</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps7:11\">PSA 7:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps50:6\">PSA 50:6</a></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ appointed as judge</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts10:42\">ACT 10:42</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John5:22\">JHN 5:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John5:27\">JHN 5:27</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John5:30\">JHN 5:30</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts17:31\">ACT 17:31</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor5:10\">2CO 5:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim4:1\">2TI 4:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim4:8\">2TI 4:8</a></p>",
